<title>
Cruise Control Switch Inspection
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70AA106001">Cruise Control Switch Removal and Installation</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove driver air bag (inflator) module. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A8206005"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect cruise control switch connector (1) from contact coil.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check resistance between “S62-5” and “S62-6” terminals under each condition below.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If check result is not as specified, replace cruise control switch.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
Use diode range of circuit tester when checking terminals “9” and “3”.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<spec>
<title>
Cruise control switch resistance
</title>
<ptxt>
All switches released (OFF): 1,960 – 2,000 &#937;
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
MAIN (ON/OFF) switch (2) pressed (ON): Less than 2.5 &#937;
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
CANCEL switch (3) pressed (ON): 99 – 101 &#937;
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
SET/COAST switch (4) pressed (ON): 386 – 394 &#937;
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
RES/ACC switch (5) pressed (ON): 772 – 788 &#937;
</ptxt>
</spec>
